  "texts": [
    "1) Functionality of ChatGPT in information gathering  Average Score: 3.5  Interpretation: The experimental group rated ChatGPT's ability to gather information positively, noting that it adequately fulfills this function, though not exceptionally.2) Contribution to generating accurate and relevant content  Average Score: 3.3  Interpretation: ChatGPT is perceived as useful in creating content that is generally accurate and relevant, although there is room for improvement to achieve a higher level of accuracy and relevance in the generated responses.3) Usability for achieving research competencies  Average Score: 2.7  Interpretation: This dimension received the lowest score, suggesting that the experimental group found certain limitations in using ChatGPT to develop or enhance research competencies.",
    "This may indicate that, while the tool is useful, it is not fully adequate to meet all the needs related to research.",
    "Overall, ChatGPT was rated relatively positively in terms of functionality and content generation, but its capacity to contribute to the acquisition of research competencies was seen as less effective.",
    "These results suggest that while ChatGPT is a useful tool in certain aspects, it may not be sufficient to support more complex or specific research processes without the intervention of complementary methods.",
    "H. General Analysis of the Results ObtainedAccording to the analysis of the results obtained, some techniques that can improve the interaction between the user and ChatGPT include providing clear and specific instructions from the beginning, thus avoiding ambiguous instructions [34]."
